IBADAN – The inventor of the Portrait Pole Post (P3), Abiodun David Fashogbon has frowned at flagrant disregard for the copyright of his firm by Oyo State Advertising Agency (OYSAA), threatening to take a legal action against the Director-General of OYSAA, Temi Adibi who allegedly masterminded the alleged violation. Fashogbon, while speaking with newsmen in Ibadan on Saturday said some violators whom his investigation revealed was encouraged by OYSAA DG to infringe on his copyright with the adverts used for the burial of late former Oyo State Governor, Otunba Adebayo Alao-Akala in Ogbomoso metropolis. The CEO of Outdoor Out of Home (OOH), an advertising firm with a product called P3, an invention of Fizzie Republic said he decided to look away because of the long relationship he has with the Akala family and especially the person of Lamiju Akala, but want the OYSSA boss sanctioned. According to him, “If Temi Adibi did not desist from misleading the public, he will be sued along with the violators because all the documents that protected our copyright claims over the product that we invented have been long submitted to him and his office (OYSAA). We expected his office to protect the right but the reverse is the case. “This is not the first time he will be masterminding people to violate our rights, as we are in Federal High Court with 9mobile on a similar case that will come up for hearing in March 2022. “We invented this brand of advertising almost two decades ago and took bold steps to register it with the Nigeria Copyright Commission via our legal department. The commission did their investigations and found out it was our idea and we told them how we came about the initiative in writing, and our claims were accredited and thereby given the copyright certificate”.